* Although the dengue virus has tricked the immune system to infect cells and spread throughout the body, the immune system has additional defenses to fight the virus:
* Infected cells produce and release small proteins that have the ability to **interfere with viral replication**.
* They help the immune system **recognize DENV-infected cells*
